# Self-Maintenance

After completing any of the following changes, proactively check whether `.cursor/rules/` and `README.md` need updating, and inform the user:

## Triggers

- Adding, removing, or renaming source files
- Adding or removing third-party dependencies
- Changing the architecture or data flow
- Modifying `.golangci.yml` or `Makefile`
- Adding new environment variables or secrets
- Changing AI model, endpoints, or prompt structure
- Modifying GitHub Actions workflow

## What to Check

| Changed | Sync target |
|---------|-------------|
| File added/removed/renamed | `project-context.mdc` architecture section |
| New dependency | `project-context.mdc` zero-deps note, `go-standards.mdc` |
| Lint config changed | `go-standards.mdc` linter list |
| New env var / secret | `README.md` secrets table |
| Prompt structure changed | `config-editing.mdc` prompt section |
| Build/test commands changed | `project-context.mdc` build section, `README.md` |
| New repo tracked | `README.md` tracked repos table |

## Behavior

- After finishing the code change, briefly tell the user which docs/rules are now stale
- Offer to update them in the same session
- Do NOT silently skip this check
